Chile Stocks: Cap, Sudamericana de Vapores and Empresas La Polar

-- B y   J a m e s   A t t w o o d   a n d   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 
2011-03-17T20:43:25Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-17/chile-stocks-cap-sudamericana-de-vapores-and-empresas-la-polar.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Chilean trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4:09 p.m. New York time.  The Ipsa index fell 0.1 percent to 4,329.20.    Cap SA (CAP)  ,  Chile ’s largest steelmaker and iron miner,
gained 3.1 percent to 21,748 pesos, the largest increase in two
weeks. Industrial metal prices advanced on speculation that
demand may increase as  Japan  rebuilds after last week’s
earthquake and tsunami.  Cia. Sudamericana de Vapores SA (VAPORES CC) retreated 3.6
percent to 272.99 pesos. Latin America’s largest container
shipping company has dropped 14 percent in the two days since
announcing plans to sell as much as $500 million in new shares.    Empresas La Polar SA (LAPOLAR)   dropped 8.8 percent to
2,505.9 pesos, the steepest fall since October 2008. The
department-store operator had a decline in annual net income to
29.8 billion pesos ($61.3 million) from 48.1 billion pesos in
2009, according to a regulatory filing distributed after the
close of trading yesterday.  To contact the reporter on this story:
James Attwood in Santiago at 
